Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper or foil. Knead the flour and the grated lemon zest into the dough. Roll it out to a 1/4-inch thickness and using the cookie cutter, cut out 18 cookies, re-rolling the scraps. Bake for approximately 12-15 minutes, or until golden. Remove from the oven, transfer to wire rack and let cool completely. Meanwhile, beat the confectioners sugar, egg white powder and water until fluffy. Divide the frosting into 3 small bowls. Tint one yellow, one orange and one pink. Frost 6 cookies of each color. Decorate the centers with assorted M&MS(R) Brand Milk Chocolate Candies, STARBURST(R) Fruit Chews or DOVE(R) Brand Silky Smooth Milk Chocolates. Set the cookies aside for the frosting to dry. Arrange 6 cookies in each clear plastic container and tie with a ribbon. Cheer someone up and give them out to friends, neighbors or family members.